I said it was over.

26:09.000 --> 26:12.948
Now y'all need
to decide right now.

26:13.038 --> 26:18.681
<i>Are you outlaws
or ain't ya ?</i>

26:18.777 --> 26:23.385
<i>‘Cause I only ride
with outlaws.</i>

26:24.082 --> 26:25.823
We're with you, Boss.

26:25.917 --> 26:28.227
That boy is gonna pay.

26:28.320 --> 26:30.391
Then saddle up.

26:32.357 --> 26:34.735
<i>(mug)
Ain't we gonna
bury him, Boss?</i>

26:37.462 --> 26:42.036
Bury who?

26:42.667 --> 26:42.700
<i>III</i>

26:42.701 --> 26:47.701
<i>III</i>

26:57.682 --> 27:02.682
<i>III</i>

27:12.697 --> 27:14.176
<i>III</i>

27:14.265 --> 27:15.676
Josh!

27:19.337 --> 27:21.374
<i>(Sheriff)
Mr. MacManus,
good to see you.</i>

27:21.473 --> 27:23.077
How are things
at the motel?

27:23.174 --> 27:26.178
<i>(Josh)
Yeah, there was a-
there was a little trouble.</i>

27:26.277 --> 27:29.087
Anyone hurt?

27:29.180 --> 27:30.716
I'm not really sure.

27:30.815 --> 27:33.352
Her husband, a few others-
I don't know what happened.

27:33.451 --> 27:35.556
They just-
they just vanished.

27:35.654 --> 27:38.726
<i>(Sheriff)
We got 22 people
missing I know of.</i>

27:38.823 --> 27:40.598
<i>They disappeared
right like you said.</i>

27:40.692 --> 27:42.763
Hey, lieutenant,
go help her.

27:44.763 --> 27:46.174
I saw it
with my own eyes.

27:46.264 --> 27:48.301
My sister,
one minute she was there,

27:48.400 --> 27:51.677
the next minute there's a bright
light, poof, she's gone.

27:51.770 --> 27:55.377
<i>(Beth)
I told you, it was God.
He took them up to heaven.</i>

27:55.473 --> 27:57.316
<i>(Josh)
You mean, like,
from the Bible?</i>

27:57.409 --> 27:59.719
Yeah, that's what some people
have been saying, yeah.

27:59.811 --> 28:01.848
<i>(Josh)
What do they call it?
The Rapture?</i>

28:01.946 --> 28:03.357
<i>(Lieutenant)
There's no way.</i>

28:03.448 --> 28:06.292
I'm a Christian
and I'm still here.

28:06.384 --> 28:08.193
<i>I was with the pastor
about an hour ago.</i>

28:08.286 --> 28:10.527
I mean, that doesn't
make any sense.

28:10.622 --> 28:13.466
Bill said you have to
accept him in your heart

28:13.558 --> 28:15.265
and you have to repent
of all your sins

28:15.360 --> 28:19.467
and ask Jesus for forgiveness
before it's too late.

28:19.564 --> 28:21.441
<i>(Lieutenant)
Here, come on,
let's go.</i>

28:21.533 --> 28:23.012
<i>Come on.</i>

28:27.072 --> 28:29.018
You have people saying
all kinds of crazy things:

28:29.107 --> 28:30.780
aliens, terrorists.

28:30.875 --> 28:32.445
We have to deal
with what's real.

28:32.544 --> 28:34.854
We got no power,
we got no communications,

28:34.946 --> 28:37.790
people are hurt,
they're scared.

28:37.882 --> 28:39.327
And you haven't
heard anything?

28:39.417 --> 28:41.761
Well, we heard some
chatter on the CB radio.

28:41.853 --> 28:45.665
So far as we can tell,
this, whatever it was,

28:45.757 --> 28:47.168
it happened everywhere.

28:47.258 --> 28:48.669
<i>Cities are bad.</i>

28:48.760 --> 28:52.071
<i>Riots, lootin‘,
a lot of bad stuff going on.</i>

28:52.597 --> 28:54.008
Josh!

28:57.602 --> 28:59.707
It's best you stay in town
with people you can trust,

28:59.804 --> 29:01.306
at least 'til things
get back to normal.

29:01.406 --> 29:03.317
That's very kind of you,
but I gotta go.

29:03.408 --> 29:04.819
My family needs me.

29:04.909 --> 29:06.855
Hold on a second.

29:06.945 --> 29:10.154
Where you're going,
you're gonna need this.

29:10.248 --> 29:12.091
It's loaded.

29:12.183 --> 29:13.594
Thanks.

29:13.685 --> 29:15.096
<i>(Beth)
I'm coming with you.</i>

29:15.186 --> 29:16.597
No, absolutely not.

29:16.688 --> 29:18.099
You're staying here
with your grand parents.

29:18.189 --> 29:20.465
Grandma and Grandpa
are gone.

29:20.558 --> 29:21.969
What do you mean?

29:22.060 --> 29:24.438
<i>(Lieutenant)
The bikers came back
looking for blood.</i>

29:24.529 --> 29:27.442
I went out there last night,
but I got there too late.

29:27.532 --> 29:29.534
House was-
was all tore up.

29:29.634 --> 29:31.375
Frank and Marion?

29:31.469 --> 29:34.382
<i>(Sheriff)
Well, she walked in last night
with quite a tale to tell us.</i>

29:34.472 --> 29:36.713
<i>It seems Frank
and his wife,</i>

29:36.808 --> 29:39.345
they just disappeared
like the others.

29:39.444 --> 29:40.855
<i>(Beth)
I'm coming with you.</i>

29:40.945 --> 29:43.357
L.A.'s on the way,
besides, I'm supposed to.

29:43.448 --> 29:44.859
He told mel would.

29:44.949 --> 29:46.792
Who told you?

29:48.620 --> 29:50.065
Beth,
you're a good kid,

29:50.155 --> 29:52.965
but there's no possible way
I'm taking you with me.

29:53.057 --> 29:54.536
It's not gonna happen.

29:56.361 --> 29:59.035
[keys clattering]

30:02.467 --> 30:12.252
<i>III</i>

30:12.343 --> 30:13.822
<i>(Josh)
Here.</i>

30:13.912 --> 30:15.949
<i>Put that on.</i>

30:16.047 --> 30:20.189
Ew, this is gross.

30:20.285 --> 30:22.322
It'll save your life.

30:22.420 --> 30:23.831
No, it won't.

30:23.922 --> 30:25.833
What's that?

30:25.924 --> 30:27.835
<i>Just put it on.</i>

30:33.898 --> 30:36.936
<i>III</i>

30:37.035 --> 30:39.709
[motorcycle engine revving]

30:40.171 --> 30:45.171
<i>III</i>

30:55.186 --> 31:00.186
<i>III</i>

31:10.201 --> 31:15.201
<i>III</i>

31:25.216 --> 31:31.360
<i>III</i>

31:31.456 --> 31:33.527
What are we doing?

31:42.500 --> 31:43.979
[car engine stops]

32:14.866 --> 32:21.841
[car dinging]

32:32.317 --> 32:35.025
[dinging continues]

32:35.119 --> 32:36.598
[dinging SHIPS]

32:45.663 --> 32:47.472
[tires screeching]

32:52.370 --> 32:54.350
What are they doing?

32:56.541 --> 32:59.522
[engine revving]

33:00.478 --> 33:03.288
Back in the car,
slowly.

33:05.283 --> 33:09.663
[engine revving]

33:36.047 --> 33:38.493
<i>(Beth)
What was that about?</i>

33:38.583 --> 33:41.530
<i>(Josh)
I don't know
and I don't wanna know.</i>

33:41.619 --> 33:42.652
<i>III</i>

33:42.653 --> 33:47.653
<i>III</i>

33:55.967 --> 33:58.447
(Jesus)
Come to me, Cat.

33:59.070 --> 34:02.051
(female #3)
Hey Cat,
come here for a second.

34:13.583 --> 34:15.291
Not you.

34:20.690 --> 34:23.170
Have a seat.

34:28.699 --> 34:31.873
<i>(Car)
This scrap heep again?</i>

34:31.969 --> 34:34.449
You can't save it.

34:34.539 --> 34:41.514
Look honey, I know that
we have never been close.

34:42.480 --> 34:47.759
<i>(female #3)
I was way too young
to have you.</i>

34:47.851 --> 34:49.831
I admit that.

34:49.920 --> 34:53.425
<i>I didn't know
what! was doing.</i>

34:55.092 --> 34:58.768
<i>I probably still don't.</i>

34:58.863 --> 35:05.439
I want to apologize for all
of the mistakes that I've made.

35:05.536 --> 35:09.643
<i>I just want you
to know that...</i>

35:09.740 --> 35:11.777
That I love you.

35:14.011 --> 35:16.184
You have nothing
to apologize for.

35:16.280 --> 35:18.590
<i>Maybe I'm tougher
than you think.</i>

35:18.683 --> 35:20.924
ls that what
you're trying to prove?

35:21.018 --> 35:22.964
<i>That you're tough?</i>

35:23.054 --> 35:28.970
You're so smart
and passionate.

35:29.060 --> 35:31.904
Now, don't
get stuck here.

35:31.996 --> 35:35.808
Go do something
with your life.

35:35.900 --> 35:39.245
I like it here.

35:39.337 --> 35:40.748
I belong here.

35:40.838 --> 35:44.445
You're never gonna get
the love that you deserve here.

35:44.542 --> 35:49.321
<i>Not from me,
certainly not from your father:</i>

35:49.413 --> 35:51.120
He lost interest in you
the moment he saw

35:51.215 --> 35:52.990
<i>that you weren't a boy.</i>

35:53.084 --> 35:54.495
Who are you?

35:54.585 --> 35:56.895
What have you done
with my mom?

36:01.425 --> 36:04.895
(female #3)
My eyes have been opened

36:04.996 --> 36:11.606
and I have a peace
thatl have never had before.

36:13.638 --> 36:17.711
If you open up your
heart to Jesus, Cat,

36:17.808 --> 36:20.118
he will show you the way.

36:22.613 --> 36:25.150
<i>(Cat)
I'm finejust
the way that I am.</i>

36:25.249 --> 36:28.458
And just like your mother.

36:28.553 --> 36:32.023
Just remember,
when you're in need,

36:32.123 --> 36:34.103
you can call to Jesus.

36:34.192 --> 36:36.433
He'll be there for you.

36:37.061 --> 36:40.873
[motorcycle engine revving]

36:57.848 --> 36:59.691
<i>(Josh)
Oh, now what?</i>

37:01.586 --> 37:03.259
<i>(Beth)
What's going on?</i>

37:03.354 --> 37:05.459
<i>(Josh)
Look, up ahead.</i>

37:06.958 --> 37:09.734
<i>(Beth)
What are they doing?</i>

37:09.827 --> 37:11.397
<i>(Josh)
Nothing good.</i>

37:11.495 --> 37:12.906
<i>(Beth)
What do we do?</i>

37:12.997 --> 37:14.670
<i>(Josh)
It'll take hours
to go another way.</i>

37:14.765 --> 37:16.244
<i>I gotta get home.</i>

37:17.902 --> 37:19.381
<i>(Beth)
Josh!</i>

37:19.904 --> 37:24.614
<i>III</i>

37:24.709 --> 37:26.279
Get your head down!

37:27.678 --> 37:28.554
[gun firing]

37:30.448 --> 37:31.859
Hold on!

37:31.949 --> 37:32.324
[glass shattering]

37:34.652 --> 37:37.929
[gunfire]

37:38.656 --> 37:42.798
<i>III</i>

37:42.893 --> 37:44.930
<i>(Josh)
What is wrong
with these people?</i>

37:45.029 --> 37:48.442
It's been, what, 12 hours
since the power went out?

37:48.532 --> 37:50.671
They can all feel it.

37:50.768 --> 37:53.715
It's the end.
Can't you feel it too?

37:53.804 --> 37:59.413
It's like all the beauty
and love in the world is gone.

38:00.978 --> 38:03.151
God's grace is gone.

38:05.716 --> 38:07.696
I don't feel much since-

38:09.520 --> 38:13.525
<i>(female #2 voiceover)
Now, fear the target.</i>

38:13.624 --> 38:16.400
<i>Kill the target.</i>

38:16.494 --> 38:18.371
<i>You believe nothing.</i>

38:18.462 --> 38:20.442
<i>Kill the target.</i>

38:20.531 --> 38:21.976
<i>Fear is impossible.</i>

38:22.066 --> 38:24.171
<i>Find the target,
kill the target.</i>

38:24.268 --> 38:27.306
<i>There's no fear;
there is no mercy.</i>

38:30.908 --> 38:35.908
<i>III</i>

38:45.923 --> 38:50.923
<i>III</i>

39:00.938 --> 39:05.938
<i>III</i>

39:15.953 --> 39:24.395
<i>III</i>

39:35.573 --> 39:40.318
[radio static]

39:43.314 --> 39:46.124
<i>(male on radio)
Good ladies and gentlemen,</i>

39:46.217 --> 39:47.855
<i>once again,
this is Gene Daughtry</i>

39:47.952 --> 39:51.627
<i>from the Power on Glory
Broadcasting Newark.</i>

39:51.722 --> 39:55.226
<i>We are back
on the air for now.</i>

39:55.326 --> 40:00.742
<i>Those of you just tuning in,
Pastor Kelson, well--</i>

40:00.831 --> 40:03.869
<i>well he's been
taken up to heaven,</i>

40:03.968 --> 40:08.747
<i>but before he went he
recorded a special message.</i>

40:08.839 --> 40:12.184
<i>It's a message! think
we all need to hear.</i>

40:12.276 --> 40:14.415
<i>We'll be repeating it
for as long as we can keep</i>

40:14.512 --> 40:16.549
<i>the generators running.</i>

40:16.647 --> 40:21.187
<i>Stay safe
and God have mercy on us all.</i>

40:21.285 --> 40:23.424
<i>(Pastor Kelson)
This is Pastor Kelson.</i>

40:23.521 --> 40:26.331
<i>In the Gospel of Matthew
our Lord says,</i>

40:26.424 --> 40:29.098
<i>“No one knows about
that day or hour,</i>

40:29.193 --> 40:32.367
<i>“not even the angels
in heaven, nor the Son,</i>

40:32.463 --> 40:34.500
<i>but only the Father.“</i>

40:34.598 --> 40:36.874
<i>No man can know the hour.</i>

40:36.967 --> 40:40.210
<i>The Lord will come for us
in his own time.</i>

40:40.304 --> 40:42.978
<i>We're told to look towards
that day in anticipation</i>

40:43.073 --> 40:45.280
<i>of laying down
our earthy burdens,</i>

40:45.376 --> 40:48.255
<i>but we cannot know the hour.</i>

40:48.345 --> 40:51.155
<i>So worry not about
the signs in the sky</i>

40:51.248 --> 40:54.491
<i>and instead sanctify yourself
to living as he commands</i>

40:54.585 --> 40:56.895
<i>and letting the light
of his strength</i>

40:56.987 --> 41:00.901
<i>shine through you, to your
friends and to your neighbors.</i>

41:00.991 --> 41:05.303
<i>Teach your children his ways;
don? waste a day,</i>

41:05.396 --> 41:10.436
<i>for no man can know the hour,
but the hour will come.</i>

41:10.534 --> 41:12.878
<i>And in the blink of an eye
those who are faithful</i>

41:12.970 --> 41:15.109
<i>will receive their reward.</i>

41:15.206 --> 41:18.881
<i>For the rest, there is
still hope of salvation</i>

41:18.976 --> 41:19.750
<i>if you would only-</i>

41:46.136 --> 41:49.811
<i>(Josh)
A lot of cars,
no people.</i>

41:49.907 --> 41:51.545
What does that mean?

41:52.977 --> 41:55.457
<i>(Josh)
Means ifs a trap.</i>

41:57.448 --> 41:58.859
What are you doing?

41:58.949 --> 42:00.860
Well, trap or not,
if we don't get gas here,

42:00.951 --> 42:03.761
it's the end of the line.

42:04.555 --> 42:06.228
Stay down.

42:06.323 --> 42:11.323
<i>III</i>

42:21.338 --> 42:26.338
<i>III</i>

42:36.353 --> 42:41.353
<i>III</i>

42:51.368 --> 42:56.368
<i>III</i>

43:06.383 --> 43:12.197
<i>III</i>

43:12.289 --> 43:14.269
Drop the gun, mister.

43:14.792 --> 43:22.836
<i>III</i>

43:28.005 --> 43:29.484
[guns hot]

43:38.816 --> 43:43.060
<i>(Josh's wife)
I know you don't believe,
but Jesus does love you</i>

43:43.153 --> 43:46.259
<i>and he can forgive you
if you wanna be forgiven.</i>

43:46.357 --> 43:48.701
It's never too Ia re.

43:53.230 --> 43:56.677
On your knees,
hands behind your back.

44:07.478 --> 44:11.221
Well, hey cuz,
you remember me?

44:13.984 --> 44:15.463
<i>This is for my truck.</i>

44:28.565 --> 44:33.565
<i>III</i>

44:39.943 --> 44:41.422
[car engine starting]

44:47.551 --> 44:52.551
<i>III</i>

45:02.533 --> 45:04.012
[guns hot]

45:07.705 --> 45:12.705
<i>III</i>

45:22.720 --> 45:25.564
<i>III</i>

45:27.891 --> 45:31.805
Hey, I can't
thank you enough.

45:31.895 --> 45:36.571
The generator will keep the
gas flowing for a few days.

45:36.667 --> 45:38.078
What about him?

45:38.168 --> 45:41.081
<i>(innkeeper)
Oh, uh, don't
worry about him.</i>

45:41.171 --> 45:44.846
The deputies will be by
later to deal with him.

45:44.942 --> 45:47.548
Well, thanks for the gas.

45:47.644 --> 45:50.090
Good man, Dale.

45:52.282 --> 45:54.262
[car engine starting]

45:57.688 --> 45:59.929
What do you think?
Upgrade?

46:00.023 --> 46:02.435
What is it with you and
other people's property?

46:02.526 --> 46:05.029
Those people
tried to kill us.

46:05.129 --> 46:07.370
What is it with you
and this old hunk-o-junk?

46:07.464 --> 46:09.842
What's wrong with my car?

46:16.406 --> 46:19.285
[car engine starting]

46:26.750 --> 46:28.787
I'm a good man.

46:30.120 --> 46:32.031
<i>I'm a good man.</i>

46:32.790 --> 46:34.360
I'm a good man.

46:35.559 --> 46:38.233
<i>(Josh)
That was a very dangerous
thing you did back there.</i>

46:38.328 --> 46:40.672
<i>You gotta be
more careful.</i>

46:40.764 --> 46:42.971
Don't do it again.

46:43.066 --> 46:46.104
I had things right
where I wanted 'em.

46:46.203 --> 46:47.682
Right.

46:50.073 --> 46:51.484
I had to save you.

46:51.575 --> 46:53.145
What are you
talking about?

46:53.243 --> 46:55.314
I'm the one
protecting you, remember?

46:55.412 --> 46:57.722
That's not what I heard.

46:59.483 --> 47:04.023
Okay, obviously you
wanna tell me something.

47:04.121 --> 47:08.661
I'll tell you my secret, but
only if you tell me yours first.

47:08.759 --> 47:10.636
What secret?

47:10.727 --> 47:13.139
Alright, whatever,
be that way.

47:14.965 --> 47:16.376
(female #2)
There's no fear.

47:16.466 --> 47:18.844
<i>You believe nothing.</i>

47:18.936 --> 47:21.212
<i>Fear is impossible.</i>

47:21.305 --> 47:27.085
Alright, I was
in the service.

47:27.177 --> 47:31.751
I volunteered
for special ops,

47:31.849 --> 47:35.296
where I received
extreme training.

47:35.385 --> 47:38.832
So, what, you have like a
robot brain or something?

47:38.922 --> 47:40.401
No.

47:44.862 --> 47:51.609
I don't...feel fear the
same way that other people do.

47:52.669 --> 47:55.843
<i>Fear makes a person
hesitate in times of danger;</i>

47:55.939 --> 48:00.615
it clouds the mind.

48:00.711 --> 48:02.486
They burned it out of me.

48:03.981 --> 48:05.722
Howd they do that?

48:12.656 --> 48:16.103
<i>(female #2)
We have definitive proof
that in certain rare cases,</i>

48:16.193 --> 48:19.902
soldiers who are exposed
to massive battle trauma

48:19.997 --> 48:21.635
<i>do not become ineffective;</i>

48:21.732 --> 48:25.509
instead the opposite
effect occurs.

48:25.602 --> 48:27.104
<i>Find the target.</i>

48:27.204 --> 48:28.945
<i>Kill the target.</i>

48:29.039 --> 48:31.815
<i>There is no fear,
there is no mercy.</i>

48:31.909 --> 48:36.983
<i>Kill the target and anyone
that stands in your way.</i>

48:37.915 --> 48:46.528
<i>III</i>

48:46.623 --> 48:49.729
[speaking foreign language]

48:54.998 --> 48:58.810
[gun firing]

49:01.238 --> 49:03.411
[speaking foreign language]

49:03.840 --> 49:05.717
<i>(male)
Your target is Mehrzad,</i>

49:05.809 --> 49:08.619
<i>son of an elder warlord
and a symbol of hope</i>

49:08.712 --> 49:10.988
for the resistance.

49:11.081 --> 49:19.592
<i>III</i>

49:21.725 --> 49:23.568
[speaking foreign language]

49:40.310 --> 49:44.122
<i>(female #2)
These unique soldiers
emerge from their trauma</i>

49:44.214 --> 49:46.194
completely fearless.

49:47.851 --> 49:49.262
<i>Fear is impossible.</i>

49:49.353 --> 49:50.764
<i>You fear nothing.</i>

49:50.854 --> 49:52.629
<i>You believe nothing.</i>

49:52.723 --> 49:54.930
<i>Your life is nothing.</i>

49:55.025 --> 49:57.301
<i>Only the mission matters.</i>

49:57.394 --> 50:02.036
<i>My scientiﬁc team has isolated
the emotional conditions</i>

50:02.132 --> 50:04.009
and the chemical triggers

50:04.101 --> 50:06.308
<i>that allow for this
phenomenon to occur.</i>

50:09.706 --> 50:13.313
Imagine,
an army of soldiers

